<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="rule-v">rule <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ruːl/    美 /ruːl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>统治；支配：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>rule</strong> (<strong>over</strong>) a country
统治国家</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In the 18th century California was ruled by Spain. 
在18世纪，加利福尼亚由西班牙统治。</p><footer>人教⑧ – 1</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="rule-out">rule out</h3>
<p>1.<strong>排除；取消：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We can’t rule out the possibility that he’ll come after all. 
我们不能排除他最终会来的可能性。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The experiment has <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (排除) the possibility of the existence of any life on that planet, but it does not mean there is no life on other planets. (rule)  （2010 江苏改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. ruled out  </p></div>